& [CurrentAttentionRuntimeRegistryState] is the live semantic registry for active attention
  + [registry_status] is active
  + [registry_scope] is semantic cognition operating loop over functional LM Studio worker lane
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_semantic_cognition_operating_loop_001
  + [active_frame_count] is 1
  + [suspended_frame_count] is 0
  + [closed_frame_count] is 0
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [registry_outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, worker mutation authority, broad task competence, and unrelated Pinky worktree changes

  = must: update this state when focus materially changes
  = must: preserve return anchors before closing or suspending frames
  = must: keep the registry semantic and visible, not native-runtime or hidden-state based
  = should: stay compact enough for context-compression re-entry

& [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_SemanticCognitionOperatingLoop001] is the active semantic stack frame for the semantic cognition operating loop
  + [frame_id] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_semantic_cognition_operating_loop_001
  + [frame_state] is active
  + [parent_frame] is none
  + [child_frame_set] is functional_lmstudio_lane, one_minute_heartbeat, operating_loop_tick_001, task_frame_launch_queue_next, commit_receipt
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [frame_trace] is SemanticCognitionOperatingLoop.sop, task_manager_loop.py, 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_001.sop, LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane.sop, and CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [focus_register] is commit-report-review-step-in-again routine
  + [question_register] is how to prevent completed work from falsely ending the task-manager process while preserving safety boundaries
  + [delineation_register] is inside clock tick, proof state, balance state, drive state, next step, and outside stop or block conditions
  + [periphery_register] is one-minute heartbeat, terminal-completion heuristic, running clock, task-frame launch queue, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is create_operating_loop_contract, implement_tick_runtime, create_heartbeat, emit_tick_001, update_reentry_state
  + [evidence_register] is automation sop-loop-reentry, operating_loop_tick_001, runtime tests, and source-preserved directive
  + [wisdom_register] is a task manager must turn proof into a next-step selection, not into a false terminal state
  + [caution_register] is the loop must stop or block for explicit user stop, credentials, destructive actions, unclear authority, or unsafe PC control
  + [balance_register] is stable because tick_001 has proof_state validated, clock_state running, drive_state continue, and outside preserved
  + [integration_register] is pending commit, push, and next task-frame launch queue
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, broad local-worker readiness, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

(current_attention_runtime_registry_state) :active_root_frame: /semantic_register_set and return_anchor/ |registry_outside|
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_semantic_cognition_operating_loop_001
  + [semantic_register_set] is focus, question, delineation, periphery, operation, evidence, Wisdom, Caution, balance, and integration registers
